cs.AI, cs.HC, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.SY

Reasoning: 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is the most likely category as the paper discusses a new method of incorporating human verbal instruction with Reinforcement Learning to improve the human-agent interaction.
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is also likely as the paper focuses on the interaction between humans and agents, specifically on frustration as a human factor metric.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is relevant as the paper discusses existing machine learning algorithms and compares the performance of the proposed method with a state-of-the-art IML algorithm.
- cs.RO (Robotics) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of RL to teach agents how to perform tasks.
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is relevant as the paper discusses the use of RL to control the behavior of agents.
